### HYMN CXXXIX

#### A hymn to the Asvins

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2013901">1</span></span>To help and
favour Vatsa now, O Asvins, come ye hitherward.  
  Bestow on him a dwelling spacious and secure, and keep malig-  
   nites afar.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2013902">2</span></span>All
manliness that is in heaven, with the Five Tribes, or in mid-  
   air,  
  Bestow, ye Asvins, upon us.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2013903">3</span></span>Remember
Kārnva first of all among the singers,, Asvins, who  
  Have thought upon your wondrous deeds.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2013904">4</span></span>Asvins, for
you with song of praise this hot oblation is effused,  
  This your sweet Soma juice, ye Lords of wealth and spoil,  
   through which ye think upon the foe.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2013905">5</span></span>Whatever ye
have done in floods, in the tree, Wonder-workers,  
   and in growing plants,  
  Therewith, O Asvins, succour me.

